    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>

                <p>your favors of aug<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> the 30<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> &amp; sep<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 5<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> are before. the cargo I dare say will come safely but I fear I
                    shall not soon have leisure to inspect it on acc<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> of
                    my <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0012">welsh Tour</title></bibl>.
                    Inclosed is an order for <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0231">Flora
                            Scotica</title></bibl>. I scarce give any away as I must not hurt
                    <persName ref="pe0139">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lightfoot</persName>.
                    <persName ref="pe0226">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Panton</persName> has just
                    called on me &amp; desires to be remembered to you.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am Dear Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> affect. humble
                            serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>

                <dateline>Sept<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 26<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></dateline></closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>The book you mention will be welcome.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom house</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburgh</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
